"title": "6745: sanctification, nature and basis of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6745",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The process of renewal and consecration by which believers are made holy through the work of the Holy Spirit. Sanctification is the consequence of justification and is dependent upon a person being in a right relationship with God.</p>\n<h2>Sanctification is grounded in the holiness of God</h2>\n<h3>God is holy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:7\">EZK 39:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:32\">LEV 22:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:19\">JOS 24:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:4\">PSA 30:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:9\">HOS 11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:3\">ISA 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:10\">REV 6:10</a></p>\n<h3>God demands that his people should reflect his holiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44-Lev11:45\">LEV 11:44–11:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:7-Lev20:8\">LEV 20:7–20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:11\">HEB 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Sanctification is the will of God for his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3\">1TH 4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:10\">EPH 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:1-1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:1–1:2</a></p>\n<h2>The basis for sanctification</h2>\n<h3>God's election of his people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:2\">1CO 1:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4-Eph1:11\">EPH 1:4–1:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:9\">1TH 5:9</a></p>\n<h3>The atoning death of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12\">HEB 13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:11\">ROM 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:4\">ROM 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:2\">ROM 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10-Heb10:14\">HEB 10:10–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>The grace of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:69-Luke1:75\">LUK 1:69–1:75</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:13\">PHP 2:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:10\">HEB 12:10</a></p>\n<h3>The work of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The word of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:17\">JHN 17:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:26\">EPH 5:25–5:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:16\">2TI 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>The need for sanctification</h2>\n<h3>The universal sinfulness of humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:6\">ISA 64:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:14-Job15:15\">JOB 15:14–15:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:5\">PSA 51:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:12–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:3\">EPH 2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Enslavement to evil can only be broken through the death of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:34-John8:36\">JHN 8:34–8:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:16-Rom6:18\">ROM 6:16–6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:7\">ROM 8:5–8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:17-Eph4:24\">EPH 4:17–4:24</a></p>\n<h3>The need for renewal and growth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1-Rom12:2\">ROM 12:1–12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:10\">COL 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3-1Thess4:6\">1TH 4:3–4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:1-Heb6:3\">HEB 6:1–6:3</a></p>\n<h2>The nature of sanctification</h2>\n<h3>A process which has already been initiated</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:2\">1CO 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a></p>\n<h3>A process of growth in holiness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1-Rom12:3\">ROM 12:1–12:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:15\">EPH 4:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3-1Thess4:7\">1TH 4:3–4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:14\">HEB 12:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:1-1Pet2:3\">1PE 2:1–2:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Consecration to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:29\">EXO 32:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:5\">1CH 29:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:26\">PRO 23:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a></p>",
